<![CDATA[<div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt; text-align: right; font-family: arial; "><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; "><font class="Apple-style-span" size="6" color="#000066">The International School</font></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt; text-align: right; font-family: arial; "><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; "><font class="Apple-style-span" size="6" color="#000066">of Moscow</font></span></div><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: right; "><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" size="4"><i>Part of The British Schools Group</i></font></div><div style="font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: right; "><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#c0c0c0" face="Arial, sans-serif" size="6"><b><i><br></i></b></font></div><div style="font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: right; "><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" size="1"><i><br></i></font></div><div style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; text-align: left; "><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 5px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 5px; "><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></span></font></div><div style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; text-align: left; "><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 5px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 5px; "><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},</font></span></font></div><div style="font-family: arial; text-align: right; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); "><span style="font-size: 12pt; ">&nbsp;</span></div>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">As you may be aware, Ms. Ruffin received
some wonderful news last term. She is expecting a son with her long time
partner Mr. Charlton. I am sure that you would join us in expressing our
delight and sincere congratulations.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">Of course this does mean that Ms. Ruffin
will require maternity leave to support the addition to the family. This will
begin at half term from Monday 23<sup>rd</sup> February. She will be away for
the rest of the school year. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">I am pleased to announce that we have
secured an excellent replacement to the Year Four team. Ms. Alice Nixon is
presently completing visa paperwork in the UK but will join us from Monday 4<sup>th</sup>
February. She has experience of teaching in Year 4 and is an able and enthusiastic
professional.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">By joining us at that time Ms. Nixon will
enjoy the opportunity to work alongside Ms. Ruffin for three weeks prior to
taking over the class.&nbsp; This period will
enable a smooth transition for all concerned. Mr. Etheridge will continue to
support in the class for the remainder of the year.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">Our intention is to present reports <u>for
that class only</u>, one week earlier on Friday the 15<sup>th</sup> of February
so that Parent Teacher Consultations can take place with both Ms. Ruffin and
Ms. Nixon present in the week beginning the 18<sup>th</sup> February. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">This arrangement will offer an opportunity
for parents and teacherMaternity to meet before the break in preparation for the rest of
the year. More details will follow on this in the near future.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">Thanks very much for your understanding and
support.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">Best regards,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US">Paul Seedhouse<o:p></o:p></span></p>

